Usage:
  lark-cli drive [flags]
  lark-cli drive [command]

Available Commands:
  +add-comment                 Add a comment to doc/docx/file/sheet/slides; file targets support selected extensions and full comments only
  +create-folder               Create a folder in Drive
  +create-shortcut             Create a Drive shortcut in another folder
  +delete                      Delete a file or folder in Drive
  +download                    Download a file from Drive to local
  +export                      Export a doc/docx/sheet/bitable to a local file with limited polling
  +export-download             Download an exported file by file_token
  +import                      Import a local file to Drive as a cloud document (docx, sheet, bitable)
  +inspect                     Inspect a Lark document URL to get its type, title, and canonical token (with wiki unwrapping)
  +move                        Move a file or folder to another location in Drive
  +pull                        One-way file-level mirror of a Drive folder onto a local directory (Drive → local)
  +push                        File-level mirror of a local directory onto a Drive folder (local → Drive; remote-only directories are not removed)
  +status                      Compare a local directory with a Drive folder by exact hash or quick modified_time
  +sync                        Two-way sync between a local directory and a Drive folder
  +task_result                 Poll async task result for import, export, drive move/delete, wiki move, wiki delete-space, or wiki delete-node operations
  +upload                      Upload a local file to Drive
  +version-delete              Delete a specific historical version of a Drive file
  +version-get                 Download a specific version of a Drive file
  +version-history             List the version history of a Drive file
  +version-revert              Revert a Drive file to a specific historical version
